---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Compliance Services | Bluebonnet CyberWorks">
  <section class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">Compliance Services</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
      We help organizations simplify cybersecurity compliance, meet industry standards, and stay audit-ready.
      Whether you're navigating frameworks like PCI-DSS, HIPAA, or NIST 800-171—we’ll guide you through it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">PCI-DSS</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Ensure your payment systems meet all 12 requirements with expert-led gap assessments and implementation support.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">NIST 800-171</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">We guide defense contractors and research institutions through control implementation, SSPs, and POA&Ms.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">HIPAA</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Support for healthcare organizations and vendors to protect ePHI and satisfy Security and Privacy Rule requirements.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-2">CMMC</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Support for CMMC readiness, scoring, and gap analysis—tailored for small contractors in the DoD supply chain.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="text-center mt-16">
    <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-blue-800 text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition">
      Request a Free Consultation
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
